&lt;p&gt;Respiratory Medicine&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Band 7 Senior Sister/ Charge Nurse – Ward 24 Good Hope Hospital&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;(Full time)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward 24 is an acute respiratory ward with level 2 patients requiring Non Invasive Ventilation and critically ill patients from ITU. The ward is part of the Respiratory Department, at The University Hospital, Birmingham Foundation Trust.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the senior sister/ charge nurse you will be an effective and strong leader, highly motivated, a credible role model and have the ability to influence as well as innovate. We are looking for someone who is passionate and enthusiastic about patient safety and improving the patient experience and will inspire the ward team&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a senior sister/ charge nurse, you will be supporting the Matron for Respiratory services to provide and deliver a robust service for all inpatients at Good Hope Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you looking for a challenge and have substantial post registration experience of which a minimum of 2 years should be at Band 6 or equivalent in an acute Respiratory/Medicine environment then please contact Matron Debbie Williams on: 07772 287 709 or email: debbie.williams@heartofengland.nhs.uk for more information.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date 15th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pre- interview assessments will be held on 25th November 2020 and if successfully complete this process, you will proceed to the interview, date to be confirmed.&lt;/p&gt;
